[SN]TITLE[SN]
Van driver dragged along road in east Belfast hijacking

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A van driver has sustained a serious head injury after he was dragged along the road by a hijacker who stole his vehicle in east Belfast.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The motorist was threatened by the man, who was demanding money, at about 14:10 BST on Friday.
As he tried to leave the van on the passenger side, the hijacker drove off and he was dragged along the Old Milltown Road in Castlereagh.
His injuries are not thought to be life-threatening.
The stolen van was later recovered a short distance away at Minnowburn Drive.
Police have appealed for anyone with information to contact them.
